Proposed law requires the DPS&C, OMV, to establish a special prestige motor vehicle
license plate to be known as the "Conserve Louisiana" plate, provided there is a minimum
of 1,000 applicants for such plates. Further requires that the license plates be restricted to
use on passenger cars, pick up trucks, recreational vehicles, and vans. Further directs the
DPS&C, OMV, to create this special prestige license plate when the applicable statutory
provisions are met and the dept.'s electronic vehicle and registration system is updated to
accommodate the creation of the new plates.
Proposed law requires the secretary work in conjunction with the Department of Wildlife
and Fisheries to select the color and design of the plate, provided it is in compliance with
present law. The design shall include the words "Conserve Louisiana".
Proposed law requires the special prestige license plate be issued, upon application to any
citizen of La. in the same manner as any other motor vehicle license plate.
Proposed law requires the fee for the plate be $50 in addition to the standard motor vehicle
registration license fee, and a handling fee of $3.50 for each plate to be retained by the
department to offset a portion of administrative costs.
Proposed law requires the revenues realized from the $50 fee imposed by proposed law be
deposited immediately upon receipt in the state treasury. After compliance with the
requirements of proposed law relative to the Bond Security and Redemption Fund, and prior
to money being placed in the state general fund, the state treasurer must place an amount
equal to those revenues in the Conservation Fund, after complying with the requirements of
present law.
Proposed law requires the secretary promulgate and adopt rules and regulations as are
necessary to implement the provisions of proposed law.
Present law created within the Conservation Fund a special account known as the "waterfowl
account" which consists of those revenues collected from the sale of the Ducks Unlimited
license plates. Further requires the funds be used solely for the purpose of conserving,
restoring, and enhancing migratory waterfowl habitat in La. Additionally requires that the
specific expenditures of the proceeds be made in consultation with La. Ducks Unlimited,
provided that La. Ducks Unlimited contributes an amount each fiscal year equal to the
amount of funds collected from the sale of the license plate placed into the "waterfowl
account".
Proposed law removes present law.
Present law created within the Conservation Fund a special account known as the "quail
account" which consists of those revenues collected from the sale of the La. Quail Forever
license plates. Further requires the revenues be subject to the same requirements as provided
for other revenues placed in the Conservation Fund in present law. Additionally requires the
funds be used solely for the purpose of conserving, restoring, and enhancing quail habitat
in La.
Proposed law removes present law.
Proposed law directs the DPS&C, OMV, to credit the existing amount of revenue generated
from the La. Quail Forever and Ducks Unlimited special prestige plates to the appropriate
organizations as provided in proposed law by January 1, 2027.
Effective upon signature of the governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
